President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. These nominations include William Beach of Kansas for Commissioner of Labor Statistics, Irving Dennis of Ohio for Chief Financial Officer at the Department of Housing and Urban Development, Steven Gardner of Kentucky for Director of the Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement, Kenneth L. Marcus of Virginia for Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights at the Department of Education, M. Lee McClenny of Washington for Ambassador Extraordinary & Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Paraguay, Carlos Trujillo of Florida for Permanent Representative of the United States to the Organization of American States, Peter Hendrick Vrooman of New York for Ambassador Extraordinary & Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Rwanda. Additionally, President Trump announced his intent to appoint Eddie Joe Williams of Arkansas as the Federal Representative to the Southern States Energy Board, and John Zangardi of Pennsylvania as Chief Information Officer at the Department of Homeland Security. He also announced his intent to designate David Kautter of Virginia as Acting Commissioner of Internal Revenue.